%% Diagram: Tombstone garbage collection — stability vs grace window
%% Type: sequence
%%{init: {'htmlLabels': false}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    participant A as Replica A
    participant B as Replica B
    participant C as Replica C
    Note over A,B,C: x is removed; tombstone t(x) created
    A->>A: remove(x) → t(x)
    A-->>B: sync t(x)
    A-->>C: sync t(x) (delayed)
    Note over A,B,C: Stability check: A waits until<br/>every replica acks t(x)
    B-->>A: ack t(x)
    C-->>A: ack t(x) (after recovery)
    Note over A,B,C: Now safe to drop t(x) everywhere
    A->>A: GC t(x)
    B->>B: GC t(x)
    C->>C: GC t(x)
    Note over A,B,C: Time-based shortcut (Cassandra-style)<br/>drop after gc_grace_seconds<br/>RISK: a node returning after the<br/>grace window can resurrect x
